### Payment Integration Testing

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@userToken = YOUR_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN

### 1. [USER] Reserve Tickets (Creates PENDING Purchase)
# @name reserve
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets/reserve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
    "eventId": 1,
    "tierId": 1,
    "quantity": 1,
    "paymentMethod": "AMOLE"
}

### 2. [USER] Initialize Payment (Get Mock Checkout URL)
# Use purchaseId from Request #1
@purchaseId = {{reserve.response.body.purchaseId}}

POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/initialize
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
    "purchaseId": {{purchaseId}}
}

### 3. [USER] Verify Payment (Manual Test)
# In real flow, the Mock Gateway UI calls this automatically.
# You can also call it manually to simulate a success.
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/verify
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
    "paymentRef": "{{reserve.response.body.paymentRef}}",
    "externalRef": "EXT-MANUAL-123456"
}

### 4. [USER] Check if Tickets were issued
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets/me
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
